casebody.data:
Hunt, Appellant, v. Humphreys, Supt., Appellee.

[Cite as Hunt v. Humphreys (1988), 35 Ohio St. 3d 65.]

(No. 87-651 Decided January 27, 1988.) Everett Hunt, Jr., pro se. Anthony J. Celebrezze, Jr., attorney general, and Alexander G. Thomas, for appellee.

For the reasons stated in the judgment entry of the court of appeals below, No. 87-CA-5, dated April 8, 1987, the dismissal of appellant’s petition for a writ of habeas corpus is hereby affirmed.

Moyer, C.J., Sweeney, Locher, Holmes, Douglas, Wright and H. Brown, JJ., concur.
